-- Unipolsai to present plan to simplify capital structure in 2014 
-- 
-- Tue Apr 29, 2014 11:08AM EDT
-- None



SAN LAZZAERO DI SAVENA, Italy, April 29 (Reuters) - Italian insurer Unipolsai <US.MI> aims to present to shareholders a plan to streamline its capital structure by the end of this year, its chief executive said on Tuesday.

The objective is to have "one single category of shares represented by the ordinary ones," CEO Carlo Cimbri said at the company's annual shareholder meeting.The capital of Unipolsai includes ordinary stocks and a smaller portion of preference shares <USn.MI> <USnb.MI>, which pay higher dividends but carry no voting rights.